    {
      "question": "Which of the following equations has $2$ as a root?",
      "answer": "(A)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "A value $x = 2$ is a root if substituting it makes the equation $0$.",
          "Check (A): $x^2 - 4x + 4 = (2)^2 - 4(2) + 4 = 4 - 8 + 4 = 0$.",
          "Since $0=0$, it is a root."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 - 4x + 4 = 0 \\\\ (2)^2 - 4(2) + 4 = 0 \\\\ 4 - 8 + 4 = 0 \\\\ 0 = 0$"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "Roots of equation",
      "marks": 1,
      "type": "mcq",
      "difficulty": "simple",
