      "question": "The sum of the roots of the quadratic equation $x^2 - 9 = 0$ is",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "The equation is $x^2 + 0x - 9 = 0$.",
          "Comparing with $ax^2 + bx + c = 0$, $a=1, b=0, c=-9$.",
          "Sum of roots $= -b/a = -0/1 = 0$.",
          "Alternatively, roots are $3$ and $-3$, sum $= 3 + (-3) = 0$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 - 9 = 0 \\\\ x = \\pm 3 \\\\ \\text{Sum} = 3 + (-3) = 0$"
