      "question": "If $\\frac{1}{2}$ is a root of the equation $x^2 - mx - \\frac{5}{4} = 0$, the value of $m$ is",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Substitute $x = 1/2$ into the equation.",
          "$(1/2)^2 - m(1/2) - 5/4 = 0$.",
          "$1/4 - m/2 - 5/4 = 0$.",
          "-m/2 - 1 = 0 \\Rightarrow -m/2 = 1 \\Rightarrow m = -2$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$(\\frac{1}{2})^2 - m(\\frac{1}{2}) - \\frac{5}{4} = 0 \\\\ \\frac{1}{4} - \\frac{m}{2} - \\frac{5}{4} = 0 \\\\ -\\frac{4}{4} - \\frac{m}{2} = 0 \\\\ -1 = \\frac{m}{2} \\\\ m = -2$"
      },
